                System.out.println("Carbon is a chemical element with symbol C and atomic number 6."+ "\nIt is nonmetallic and tetravalentâ€”making four electrons available to form covalent chemical bonds." +"\n Carbon is the 15th most abundant element in the Earth's crust, and the fourth most abundant element in the universe by mass after hydrogen, helium, and oxygen."
                        + "\n Electron configuration: 1s^22s^22p^2 " +"\n Physical Properties" + "\n Phase at STP: solid" +"\n Sublimation point: 3915K" +"\n Density (near r.t.): 1.8 - 2.1g/cm^3(amorphous), 2.267g/cm^3(graphite), 3.515g/cm^3(diamond)");
