                System.out.println("Magnesium is a chemical element with symbol Mg and atomic number 12."+ "\nIt is a shiny gray solid which bears a close physical resemblance to the other five elements in the second column (group 2, or alkaline earth metals) of the periodic table." +"\n Magnesium is the ninth most abundant element in the universe."
                        + "\n Electron configuration: [Ne]3s^2 " +"\n Physical Properties" + "\n Phase at STP: solid" +"\n Melting point: 923K" + "\n Boiling point: 1363K" +"\n Density: 1.783g/cm^3(near r.t.), 1.584g/cm^3(M.P)");
